label: nauplius
definition: the first larval stage of many crustaceans, having an unsegmented body and a single eye.

label: alpha
definition: Light-limited photosynthesis; Calculated by the initial slope of the line between light intensity (x-axis) and photosynthetic rate (y-axis) in a Photosynthesis–Irradiance Response Curve (P versus E curve)

label: photoinhibition
definition: Photoinhibition, when light-intensity has a negative impact on photosynthethic production; calculated from Photosynthesis–Irradiance Response Curve (P versus E curve)

label: Fv/Fm
definition: Fv/Fm is a normalized ratio created by dividing variable fluorescence by maximum fluorescence. It is a measurement ratio that represents the maximum potential quantum efficiency of Photosystem II if all capable reaction centers were open.

label: primary production
definition: The synthesis of organic compounds/biomass from inorganic carbon dioxide.
